unishing them when they act incorrectly.\n\n- Charles\n|\nBefore you attack the porcupine, think of its quills!\n\n- Ernest\n|\nMen become wise just as they become rich, more by what they save than by what they receive.\n\n- Wilbur\n|\nSelf-disruption is akin to undergoing major surgery, but you are the one holding the scalpel.\n\n- Jay Samit, Disrupt You!: Master Personal Transformation, Seize Opportunity, and Thrive in the Era of Endless Innovation\n|\nBe of good cheer, your visions will be fulfilled in their own time.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nAsk any successfully married couple what keeps their relationship alive and they will tell you, 'interest.' It's as simple as that.\n\n- Lindsey Rietzsch, How to Date Your Spouse: A Couple's Guide to Falling and Staying in Love\n|\nGreatness can be contagious, but first there must be contact.\n\n- TemitOpe\n|\nIt's a season of life, if your granted peace, freedom and you got the right person to love.\n\n- Auliq"